comments.body:
For styling `if`/`for` I tried to be consistant but with some rules:

* if `if`/`for` expression is _simple_: inlined
  ```dart
  List<String> l1 = <String>[
    'a',
    if (b) 'b',
  ];
  List<String> l2 = <String>[
    '1',
    for (String v in l1) v,
    '2',
  ];
  ```
* if there's _simple_ `if`/`else`: inlined but `else` on new line
  ```dart
  List<String> l = <String>[
    'a',
    if (b) 'b'
    else 'c',
  ];
  ```
* if then is multi-line: split
  ```dart
  List<String> l = <String>[
    'a',
    if (c)
      getString(
        long,
        params,
        list,
      ),
  ];
  ```
* if there are other splitted `for`/`if` in the list/map: split
  ```dart
  List<String> l = <String>[
    'a',
    if (b)
      'b',
    if (c)
      getString(
        long,
        params,
        list,
      ),
  ];
  ```
* if several `for`/`if` in the same expression: split
  ```dart
  List<String> l = <String>[
    for (String v in list)
      if (condition(v))
        'b',
  ];
  ```
* special cased multiline spreads
  ```dart
  List<String> l = <String>[
      if (condition(v)) ...<String>[
        'a',
        'b',
      ],
      for (String v in list) ...<String>[
        'c',
        v,
        'd',
      ],
  ];
  ```
